{"parse":{"title":"Blue sign","pageid":47309333,"revid":810953783,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303569\">@media all and (max-width:720px){.mw-parser-output .tmulti>.thumbinner{width:100%!important;max-width:none!important}.mw-parser-output .tmulti .tsingle{float:none!important;max-width:none!important;width:100%!important;text-align:center}}</style><div class=\"thumb tmulti tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:244px;max-width:244px\"><div class=\"tsingle\" style=\"margin:1px;width:242px;max-width:242px\"><div class=\"thumbimage\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_(ENI_02323909)_mit_Leichter_Quatro_(ENI_02332894)_am_Deutschen_Eck,_Koblenz-8687.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg/240px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"135\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg/360px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg/480px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8687.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"5184\" data-file-height=\"2916\" /></a></div></div><div class=\"tsingle\" style=\"margin:1px;width:242px;max-width:242px\"><div class=\"thumbimage\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_(ENI_02323909)_mit_Leichter_Quatro_(ENI_02332894)_am_Deutschen_Eck,_Koblenz-8679.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg/240px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"135\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg/360px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg/480px-Motorfrachtschiff_Anroma_%28ENI_02323909%29_mit_Leichter_Quatro_%28ENI_02332894%29_am_Deutschen_Eck%2C_Koblenz-8679.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4750\" data-file-height=\"2672\" /></a></div></div><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"clear:left;text-align:left;background-color:transparent\"><b>Blue sign</b> activated, during <a href=\"/wiki/Starboard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Starboard\">starboard</a> passing</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:242px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG/240px-Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG\" width=\"240\" height=\"160\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG/360px-Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG/480px-Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"4752\" data-file-height=\"3168\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Blaue_Tafel_mit_wei%C3%9Fem_Funkellicht_Binnenschiff_02.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rotating-style blue sign laying flat when not active.  There is a 5&#160;cm white border and the light is in the centre</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>blue sign</b> or <b>blue board</b> is used by inland waterways vessels within the <a href=\"/wiki/Trans-European_Inland_Waterway_network\" title=\"Trans-European Inland Waterway network\">Trans-European Inland Waterway network</a> when performing a special manoeuvre or passing on the starboard side.  On navigable <a href=\"/wiki/Waterways\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Waterways\">waterways</a> vessels normally pass each other on the <a href=\"/wiki/Port_and_starboard\" title=\"Port and starboard\">port</a>-side, so the display of the blue sign and flashing white light signal intention to pass each other on the <a href=\"/wiki/Starboard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Starboard\">starboard</a>-side.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> This process is known as <b>blue boarding</b> or historically <b>blue flagging</b>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-harwood_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-harwood-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-martin_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-martin-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-pilkington_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pilkington-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <i><i><span lang=\"fr\" title=\"French language text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Code_Europ%C3%A9en_des_Voies_de_la_Navigation_Int%C3%A9rieure\" title=\"Code Europ\u00e9en des Voies de la Navigation Int\u00e9rieure\">Code Europ\u00e9en des Voies de la Navigation Int\u00e9rieure</a></span></i></i> (CEVNI) regulations require upstream vessels operating on the opposite side to display a light-blue sign and scintillating (flashing) white light.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cevni-6.06_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cevni-6.06-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  Article 3.03 states that the board must be rectangular and 1-metre \u00d7 1-metre for large vessels, or 0.6-metres \u00d7 0.6-metres for small vessels.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cevni-3.03_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cevni-3.03-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The presence and status of the blue sign is transmitted by the ship's Inland-<a href=\"/wiki/Automatic_Identification_System\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Automatic Identification System\">Automatic Identification System</a> (Inland-AIS) transponder to other vessels.  The status of the sign is transmitted using two bits of the \"regional application flags\"/\"special manoeuvre field\" in the AIS position reports.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>  This must be transmitted every ten seconds.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Blue_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Varen doe je samen!; Numericanal; Department of Waterways; Rotterdam Harbour; Groningen Seaports; Amsterdam Harbour; Koninklijke Schuttevaer; ANWB; Watersportverbond; HISWA; SRN (2014). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20150723230511/http://www.varendoejesamen.nl/sites/default/files/folders/EN%20The%20Blue%20Sign.pdf\">\"The Blue Sign\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.varendoejesamen.nl/sites/default/files/folders/EN%20The%20Blue%20Sign.pdf\">the original</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span> on 2015-07-23.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Blue+Sign&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.au=Varen+doe+je+samen%21&amp;rft.au=Numericanal&amp;rft.au=Department+of+Waterways&amp;rft.au=Rotterdam+Harbour&amp;rft.au=Groningen+Seaports&amp;rft.au=Amsterdam+Harbour&amp;rft.au=Koninklijke+Schuttevaer&amp;rft.au=ANWB&amp;rft.au=Watersportverbond&amp;rft.au=HISWA&amp;rft.au=SRN&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.varendoejesamen.nl%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Ffolders%2FEN%2520The%2520Blue%2520Sign.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-harwood-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-harwood_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Harwood, Margaret (2015). \"Appendix\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=yG91CAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA162\"><i>Cruising the Inland Waterways of France &amp; Belgium</i></a> (18th ed.). <a href=\"/wiki/The_Cruising_Association\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Cruising Association\">The Cruising Association</a>. p.&#160;162. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-326-11343-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-326-11343-8\">978-1-326-11343-8</a>. <q>Blue Flagging. Especially on rivers, look out for ships or barges with a blue flag or board display on the starboard side of the wheelhouse.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Appendix&amp;rft.btitle=Cruising+the+Inland+Waterways+of+France+%26+Belgium&amp;rft.pages=162&amp;rft.edition=18th&amp;rft.pub=The+Cruising+Association&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-326-11343-8&amp;rft.aulast=Harwood&amp;rft.aufirst=Margaret&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DyG91CAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA162&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-martin-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-martin_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Martin, Marian (2013). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=yTJLAAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PT161\"><i>The European Waterways: A User's Guide</i></a>. A &amp; C Black. p.&#160;161. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781472901545\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781472901545\">9781472901545</a>. <q>\u2026 meetings are conducted what is colloquially known as 'blue boarding'</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+European+Waterways%3A+A+User%27s+Guide&amp;rft.pages=161&amp;rft.pub=A+%26+C+Black&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=9781472901545&amp;rft.aulast=Martin&amp;rft.aufirst=Marian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DyTJLAAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPT161&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation magazine\">Clark Jr., Fred C. (April 1974).  Smyth, Peter R., ed. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=1rWcotTBFdEC&amp;pg=PA138\">\"Cruising Europe\"</a>. <i>Motor Boating &amp; Sailing</i>. Whiting, John R. p.&#160;138. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number\" title=\"International Standard Serial Number\">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/issn/1531-2623\">1531-2623</a>. <q>Lots of blue flagging, as upbound vessels try to stay in the shadow of the current, and call for starboard-to-starboard passing.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Cruising+Europe&amp;rft.pages=138&amp;rft.pub=Whiting%2C+John+R.&amp;rft.date=1974-04&amp;rft.issn=1531-2623&amp;rft.aulast=Clark+Jr.&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D1rWcotTBFdEC%26pg%3DPA138&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-pilkington-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-pilkington_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Pilkington, Roger (1964). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=HuI7AAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA6\"><i>Small boat through Germany</i></a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(originally published 1963)</span>. St. Martin's Press. <q>we had already rigged an arrangement for blue flagging\u2014a flag of Oxbridge blue run up on the starboard side being an indication that a vessel proceeding downstream on the Rhine, Meuse, Main, Neckar, Lahn, Ems, Weser, Elbe or Seine wishes to meet an approaching ship starboard to starboard instead of port to port. Or, more simply, that the skipper is keeping to the left instead of the right because he wants the current, or can't steer properly</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Small+boat+through+Germany&amp;rft.pub=St.+Martin%27s+Press&amp;rft.date=1964&amp;rft.aulast=Pilkington&amp;rft.aufirst=Roger&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DHuI7AAAAMAAJ%26pg%3DPA6&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-cevni-6.06-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-cevni-6.06_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Inland Transport Committee; Working Party on Inland Water Transport. \"Rules of the Road\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/trans/doc/finaldocs/sc3/ECE-TRANS-SC3-115-Rev.5e_WEB.pdf\"><i>European Code for Inland Waterways</i></a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span> (5th ed.). <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations_Economic_Commission_for_Europe\" title=\"United Nations Economic Commission for Europe\">United Nations Economic Commission for Europe</a>. p.&#160;53. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-92-1-117090-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-92-1-117090-0\">978-92-1-117090-0</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 July</span> 2015</span>. <q>Article 6.04 \u2013 Meeting: Normal rules \u2026 4. Vessels proceeding upstream which leave the course of those proceeding downstream on their starboard side shall in good time and to starboard: \u2026 Display a light blue board in conjunction with a bright scintillating white light.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Rules+of+the+Road&amp;rft.btitle=European+Code+for+Inland+Waterways&amp;rft.pages=53&amp;rft.edition=5th&amp;rft.pub=United+Nations+Economic+Commission+for+Europe&amp;rft.isbn=978-92-1-117090-0&amp;rft.au=Inland+Transport+Committee&amp;rft.au=Working+Party+on+Inland+Water+Transport&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.unece.org%2Ffileadmin%2FDAM%2Ftrans%2Fdoc%2Ffinaldocs%2Fsc3%2FECE-TRANS-SC3-115-Rev.5e_WEB.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-cevni-3.03-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-cevni-3.03_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Inland Transport Committee; Working Party on Inland Water Transport. \"Visual Signals (Marking) on Vessels\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/trans/doc/finaldocs/sc3/ECE-TRANS-SC3-115-Rev.5e_WEB.pdf\"><i>European Code for Inland Waterways</i></a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span> (5th ed.). United Nations Economic Commission for Europe. p.&#160;20. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-92-1-117090-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-92-1-117090-0\">978-92-1-117090-0</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 July</span> 2015</span>. <q>Article 3.03 \u2013 Boards, flags and pennants \u2026 rectangular. \u2026 (a) \u2026 neither the length nor the width is less than 1 m or, in the case of small craft, less than 0.60 m;</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Visual+Signals+%28Marking%29+on+Vessels&amp;rft.btitle=European+Code+for+Inland+Waterways&amp;rft.pages=20&amp;rft.edition=5th&amp;rft.pub=United+Nations+Economic+Commission+for+Europe&amp;rft.isbn=978-92-1-117090-0&amp;rft.au=Inland+Transport+Committee&amp;rft.au=Working+Party+on+Inland+Water+Transport&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.unece.org%2Ffileadmin%2FDAM%2Ftrans%2Fdoc%2Ffinaldocs%2Fsc3%2FECE-TRANS-SC3-115-Rev.5e_WEB.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation report\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ccr-zkr.org/files/documents/ris/ais20_e.pdf\">Central Commission for the Navigation of the Rhine (CCNR) Test Standard Inland AIS</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span> (Report). Vessel Tracking and Tracing Standard for Inland Navigation (2.0 ed.). 16 October 2012. pp.&#160;12\u201313<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 July</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=report&amp;rft.btitle=Central+Commission+for+the+Navigation+of+the+Rhine+%28CCNR%29+Test+Standard+Inland+AIS&amp;rft.series=Vessel+Tracking+and+Tracing+Standard+for+Inland+Navigation&amp;rft.pages=12-13&amp;rft.edition=2.0&amp;rft.date=2012-10-16&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ccr-zkr.org%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fris%2Fais20_e.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+sign\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:32007R04